    <string name="hydration_title">Why hydration matters for chronic urticaria (CU) patients?</string>
    <string name="hydration_info_header">Why Hydration Matters for Chronic Urticaria (CU) Patients:</string>
    <string name="hydration_point1">1. Supports mast cell stability: Dehydration can make your body more reactive, which may worsen histamine release—the key driver of hives and itching.</string>
    <string name="hydration_point2">2. Helps regulate body temperature: Overheating is a common trigger for hives. Good hydration helps your body cool itself more efficiently.</string>
    <string name="hydration_point3">3. Maintains skin barrier function: Well-hydrated skin is less prone to irritation and itching, reducing flare intensity.</string>
    <string name="hydration_point4">4. Improves medication tolerance: Antihistamines and other treatments tend to work more effectively when your body is well hydrated.</string>
    <string name="hydration_point5">5. Reduces flare triggers: Fatigue, stress, and dehydration often overlap—staying hydrated can help minimize these compounding triggers.</string>
    <string name="hydration_takeaway">Simple takeaway: Staying consistently hydrated can reduce flare severity and frequency and make symptoms easier to manage.</string>
